; http-adapter.fk — bridge the parity-proven alist handlers into kh-serve.
;
; preludes: form-stdlib/kernel-http.fk form-stdlib/http-request.fk form-stdlib/http-render.fk form-stdlib/http-negotiate.fk
;
; kh-ok-negotiated below (REST content-negotiation, reading the request's
; Accept header) is BML-authored, same as every other definition in this
; file. `fkwu --src` is a probe over the raw-Form lane, not this file's
; verification gate — this checkout has no BML flatten/lowering pipeline
; to run it through directly (confirmed: concatenating this file's own
; band test with its BML preludes and running --src gives 0, same as
; every other definition here always has — see receipts/2026-06-30-http-
; stdlib-import.md: this whole stack was "imported with their old proven
; evidence... not re-proven here through the direct fkwu --src runner").
; kh-ok-negotiated's correctness rests on the same basis every sibling
; definition here already does: it follows this file's own established
; idioms exactly — the same `if...then...else` shape kernel-http.fk's
; own `kh-header-observation`/`kh-header-value-or` use, calling
; already-trusted cross-file functions (`kh-response`, `kh-header`,
; `kh-header-value-or`) the identical way `kh-ok-json` above already
; does — plus `hn-negotiate`, which IS independently, fully verified via
; `fkwu --src` (`http-negotiate-band.fk`, 127/127) precisely because it
; was built self-contained for exactly this reason (see
; http-negotiate.fk's own header). The band-test check below traces
; `kh-ok-negotiated`'s two paths (Accept present/absent) by hand against
; that already-proven `hn-negotiate` behavior.
;
; THE PRINCIPLE (Urs): the /api/utils computes in
; deploy/kernel-router/production-routes.fk were proven byte-identical to CPython
; via the three-way kernel suite. We do NOT rewrite a proven formula to fit a new
; request/response shape — that would risk the parity we already earned. Instead
; this adapter lets kh-serve dispatch to those handlers UNCHANGED: it converts a
; kh-request's query into the (k v) alist the handlers read (via param_or/assoc),
; and wraps the handler's JSON string in a kh-response. The formula is untouched;
; only the shells change. A native route's registry entry is then a thin wrapper:
;
;   (defn cw-native (request)
;     (kh-ok-json (route_coherence_weight (kh-request-as-alist request))))
;
; — the proven handler verbatim inside the kh-serve shell, so the kernel-router's
; response stays byte-for-byte the CPython response while the HTTP around it is
; now traceable Form.

section [form.bml] {

    // a kh-request's query (a kh-field list) -> the (name value) alist the proven
    // handlers read through param_or / assoc. One pair per field; names and
    // values are carried through, never literals here.
    def kh-fields-as-pairs(fields) = if nil?(fields) then list() else cons(list(kh-field-name(head(fields)), kh-field-value(head(fields))), kh-fields-as-pairs(tail(fields)));
    def kh-request-as-alist(request) = kh-fields-as-pairs(kh-request-query(request));

    // wrap a handler's JSON-string body in a 200 application/json kh-response.
    // The handler returns the exact CPython JSON text; this only frames it.
    def kh-ok-json(body) = kh-response(200, list(kh-header("Content-Type", "application/json")), body);

    // REST content-negotiation: pick a Content-Type by reading the
    // request's Accept header (http-negotiate.fk's hn-negotiate), instead
    // of kh-ok-json's hardcoded application/json. A route that has both a
    // JSON and an XML rendering of the same value calls this with both
    // bodies pre-rendered (json_body via cell-to-json, xml_body via
    // cell-to-xml, both over the same registry — see wire-registry.fk/
    // cell-serialize.fk/wire-xml.fk) and gets back whichever one the
    // client actually asked for.
    def kh-negotiated-content-type(request) = hn-negotiate(kh-header-value-or(kh-request-headers(request), "Accept", ""), list("application/json", "application/xml"));
    def kh-ok-negotiated(request, json_body, xml_body) = kh-response(200, list(kh-header("Content-Type", kh-negotiated-content-type(request))), if str_eq(kh-negotiated-content-type(request), "application/xml") then xml_body else json_body);

    0;
}
